episodes.title: U.S. Justice Department reviewing more than a million newly found Epstein docs
episodes.description:
The U.S. Department of Justice says it has found more than a million more documents potentially tied to convicted sex offender Jeffrey Epstein, delaying a full release for weeks while officials redact details to protect victims.

episodes.description:

episodes.title: Latest batch of Epstein documents released by U.S. Justice department
episodes.description:
The U.S. Department of Justice has released the latest batch of documents from its investigations into sex offender Jeffrey Epstein, revealing U.S. President Donald Trump travelled on Epstein's private jet at least eight times between 1993 and 1996, according to an email in the release from a U.S. attorney. Shortly after releasing the latest trove, the Justice department stated some documents contain 'untrue and sensationalist claims' against Trump.

episodes.title: Prince Andrew to lose ‘Prince’ title, Buckingham Palace announces
episodes.description:
King Charles has stripped his brother, Andrew, of his royal title following years of controversy about his ties with the late sex offender Jeffery Epstein. Buckingham Palace said Andrew's titles, honours and lease on his home, the Royal Lodge, would be surrendered.

episodes.title: Virginia Giuffre accuses Prince Andrew of being 'entitled' in posthumous book
episodes.description:
A posthumous book by Virginia Giuffre, titled Nobody's Girl, accuses Prince Andrew of being 'entitled — as if he believed having sex with me was his birthright,' according to excerpts published in the Guardian.The book is expected to be published next week, almost six months after Giuffre took her own life.

episodes.title: National Arts Centre cuts ties with controversial Chinese dance group, Shen Yun
episodes.description:
The National Arts Centre in Ottawa will not host performances by Shen Yun in 2026. Internal emails released to CBC News show the centre worried about breaches of contract and the potential for human rights complaints over Shen Yun’s alleged mistreatment of people with disabilities. Shen Yun is affiliated with Falun Gong, a spiritual movement banned in China and at odds with that country’s government.
